Defendant Brandy M Jackson in court with attorney Daryl A. Kastenson.  Defendant Brandy M Jackson in custody.  Catelin Ringersma appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

This matter was originally scheduled for a Restitution Hearing today, however, the parties have now reached an agreement.
Defense stipulates to the amount requested by the victim's insurance company.
No objections.
Based upon the stipulation of the parties, Court AMENDED the Judgment of Conviction today and ordered defendant to PAY restitution in the amount of $8,087.73 to Sentry Insurance - claim# 92K002207.  Court "administratively" ordered the restitution to be paid over a period of probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
for Restitution Hearing filed by ADA Catelin Ringersma on behalf of the State.  Restitution Hearing scheduled on 08-27-2014 at 3:00 PM - Br. 2, Judge Donald's Court.
with attached Restitution Worksheet as to victim, Preston J.; filed.

Defendant Brandy M Jackson in court with attorney Daryl A. Kastenson.  Defendant Brandy M Jackson in custody.  Catelin Ringersma appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights form tendered to the Court.

AS TO COUNT 1:    Sentencing proceeds. Statements made by the State, defense counsel and defendant. 

Court sentenced defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT in the Wisconsin State Prisons for 4 YEARS, with credit for 52 days time served if revoked.  
INITIAL CONFINEMENT of 2 YEARS and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 2 YEARS. 

Court finds defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.
Court finds defendant is eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.

COURT STAYS sentence and places defendant on PROBATION for 3 YEARS under the supervision of the Wisconsin Department of Corrections.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION/EXTENDED SUPERVISION: 
* Comply with the standard rules of probation/extended supervision.
* SERVE 45 DAYS "condition time" as straight time.
* Complete 60 hours of community service.
* Seek and maintain full-time employment.
* Complete a job training program to enhance ability to obtain employment.
* Cooperate and participate with an AODA assessment and follow any recommended treatment.
* Maintain absolute sobriety and submit to random urine screens.
* Provide a DNA sample and PAY DNA surcharge - to be paid over a period of probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
* PAY the balance of all applicable court costs, fees, and surcharges - to be paid over a period of probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
  
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm or body armor.  
Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.
Appeal rights given.

Defendant Brandy M Jackson in court with attorney Daryl A. Kastenson.  Defendant Brandy M Jackson in custody.  Catelin Ringersma appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights form tendered to the Court.

AS TO COUNT 1:    Defendant changes plea to GUILTY "as charged". Defendant examined as to her plea, advised of her Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived her rights.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Defendant is advised she is a convicted felon and may not possess any firearms and body armor. Defendant is advised she is unable to vote in any election until civil rights are restored. Defendant further advised that if she is not a US citizen deportation is possible.
